The Blender file loader (com.jme3.scene.plugins.blender.BlenderLoader) does not store the custom properties set to the scene (in Blender) to the resulting Node object (in JMonkey).
The fix is simple. I'm too lazy to learn Git(hub) right now, though, and therefore will simply add a patch file below. :blush:
Disclaimer: I don't really know the source code of the loader very well, so someone with better knowledge should verify its correctness.

```
Index: BlenderLoader.java
===================================================================
--- BlenderLoader.java  (revision 5566)
+++ BlenderLoader.java  (working copy)
@@ -70,6 +70,7 @@
 import com.jme3.scene.plugins.blender.meshes.TemporalMesh;
 import com.jme3.scene.plugins.blender.modifiers.ModifierHelper;
 import com.jme3.scene.plugins.blender.objects.ObjectHelper;
+import com.jme3.scene.plugins.blender.objects.Properties;
 import com.jme3.scene.plugins.blender.particles.ParticlesHelper;
 import com.jme3.scene.plugins.blender.textures.TextureHelper;
 import com.jme3.texture.Texture;
@@ -235,6 +236,14 @@
     private Node toScene(Structure structure) throws BlenderFileException {
         ObjectHelper objectHelper = blenderContext.getHelper(ObjectHelper.class);
         Node result = new Node(structure.getName());
+
+        if (blenderContext.getBlenderKey().isLoadObjectProperties()) {
+            Properties properties = objectHelper.loadProperties(structure, blenderContext);
+            if (properties != null && properties.getValue() != null) {
+                objectHelper.applyProperties(result, properties);
+            }
+        }
+        
         List<Structure> base = ((Structure) structure.getFieldValue("base")).evaluateListBase();
